explanation: The solution uses a greedy approach to build the result string. It iterates over the input string, appending each character to the temporary string `t`. Then, it checks if the last character of `t` can be appended to the result string `res` without changing the lexicographical order. If so, it appends the character to `res` and removes it from `t`. Finally, it appends the remaining characters in `t` to `res`. The time complexity is O(n) because each character is processed once, and the space complexity is O(n) because the maximum size of `res` and `t` is equal to the length of the input string.

